      <accessrestrict id="aspace_a5ce3fcc8a7649fed0a50e3aee94e43d">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <arrangement id="aspace_eda659924a310687a35c55292e2f2f3c">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The materials are arranged by topic and subsequent accessions.</p>  
      </arrangement>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_4e080f59402758b6e0e22745da3070a5">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The materials contain photographs, slides, and pictures of Connecticut Hall at Yale, which was known as South Middle College from 1882 to 1905. Included are photographs of the renovation work completed in 1953.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
